
[1]vitrify

   VIT'RIFY, v.t. [L. vitrum, glass, and facio, to make.]

   To convert into glass by fusion or the action of heat; as, to vitrify
   sand and alkaline salts.

         VIT'RIFY, v.i. To become glass; to be converted into glass.

   Chimists make vessels of animal substances calcined, which will not
   vitrify in the fire.
